<paragraph id="8BB7368AD856FFD93CB4FCEE3320F8B9" blockId="3.[151,1059,851,991]" pageId="3" pageNumber="962">
D i a g n o s i s: The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D856FFD93DF7FCE9306DF80E" authorityName="Kirsch" authorityYear="1871" box="[468,594,851,872]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D856FFD93DF7FCE9306DF80E" box="[468,594,851,872]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="962">Aphelocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
KIRSCH was revised in 2005 (OPITZ 2005). This work included a key to species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D856FFD93E11FCCB312FF8E0" box="[562,784,881,902]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="962" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="copanus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D856FFD93E11FCCB312FF8E0" box="[562,784,881,902]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="962">Aphelocerus copanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens key out to 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D856FFD9382FFCCB32E5F8C5" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="962">A. lividus</emphasis>
OPITZ, from which 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D856FFD93D95FC3430ACF8C2" box="[438,659,910,932]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="962" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="copanus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D856FFD93D95FC3430ACF8C2" box="[438,659,910,932]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="962">Aphelocerus copanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens differ by showing a more rounded pronotum, more gradual elytral posterior slope, and a more narrow aedeagal ventral sinus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB7368AD856FFD93CB4FC553057FE6D" blockId="3.[151,1059,1006,1292]" pageId="3" pageNumber="962">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 4.0 mm; width 
<quantity id="4CF09B6FD856FFD93E82FC5430CEFF62" box="[673,753,1006,1028]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="962" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD856FFD93F5CFC5431EBFF62" box="[895,980,1006,1028]" captionStart="Figs 262-265" captionStartId="93.[151,191,1499,1521]" captionTargetBox="[153,1060,199,1483]" captionTargetId="figure@93.[153,1061,199,1485]" captionTargetPageId="93" captionText="Figs 262-265: Habitus; (262) Aphelocerus copanus; (263) A. ligulus; (264) A. magnipannus; (265) A. nodus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746792" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746792/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="962">Fig. 262</figureCitation>
. Color: Black, short line of white setae at base of elytral sutural margins, elytral disc with anterior and posterior white setal tufts. Head: Genae and epicranium extended; interocular depression and frontal umbo shallow; antenna (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD856FFD93F32FBFC316DFF3A" box="[785,850,1094,1116]" captionStart="Figs 1-27" captionStartId="70.[151,191,1302,1324]" captionTargetBox="[155,1057,207,1268]" captionTargetId="figure@70.[155,1058,207,1283]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="Figs 1-27: Antennae; (1) Aphelocerus nodus; (2) A. copanus; (3) A. magnipannus; (4) A. yoro; (5) A. sparicapillus; (6) A. tigra. (7) A. nolus; (8) A. ligulus; (9) Perilypus schusteri; (10) P. apunctus; (11) P. virgulatus; (12) P. izabal; (13) P. alpinus; (14) Cregya fuscomacula; (15) Phonius versus; (16) Pujoliclerus ariquemes; (17) Pelonium falcatum; (18) Pujoliclerus cnecostus; (19) P. trunculus. (20) P. sentus; (21) P. testudinatus; (22) P. catie; (23) P. flavidus; (24) P. convexus; (25) P. meloinus; (26) P. mexicoensis; (27) P. tuxtlas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746746/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="962">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) capitate, funicular antennomeres filiform, progressively shorter and wider towards capitulum, capitulum not compact; eyes finely facetted, eye narrower than frons (EW/FW 12/35). Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD856FFD93D2CFB243353FFD2" box="[271,364,1182,1204]" captionStart="Figs 153-162" captionStartId="78.[151,191,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[174,1045,215,1409]" captionTargetId="figure@78.[153,1061,200,1429]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="Figs 153-162: Pronota; (153) Agnatis vaurieae; (154) Pelonium atrigonatium; (155) Pujoliclerus variolus; (156) Epiphloeus prolixicornus; (157) Sirpa latiflava; (158) Neorthopleura turnbowi; (159) Aphelocerus yaguare; (160) A. copanus; (161) Amboakis mitaraka; (162) Ellipotoma makrosa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746762/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="962">Fig. 160</figureCitation>
) slightly transverse, very finely punctate; side margins strongly arcuate (PW/PL 66/62); elytra moderately convex, disc with striae of very small setiferous punctures, posterior slope gradual (EL/EW 180/55). Abdomen: Pygidium transverse 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D856FFD93CDDFB4C333AFE6A" bold="true" box="[254,261,1270,1292]" pageId="3" pageNumber="962">/</emphasis>
scutiform; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD856FFD93E2FFB4C3057FE6D" box="[524,616,1270,1292]" captionStart="Figs 201-206" captionStartId="83.[151,191,1264,1286]" captionTargetBox="[153,1059,191,1248]" captionTargetId="figure@83.[153,1059,191,1248]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Figs 201-206: Aedeagi; (201) Aphelocerus copanus; (202) A. ligulus; (203) A. magnipannus; (204) A. nodus; (205) A. nolus; (206) A. sparicapillus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746772/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="962">Fig. 201.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
